HEADWORD: Post-obit bond
<hw>Post-o"bit bond`</hw> }</mhw>. <ety>[Pref. <ets>post-</ets> +
<ets>obit</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A bond in which the
obligor, in consideration of having received a certain sum of money,
binds himself to pay a larger sum, on unusual interest, on the death of
some specified individual from whom he has expectations.</def>
<rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Postoblongata</ent>⟦br⟧
